1.title: Underworld
1.plot: Kirito, along with his childhood friend, Eugeo, has been tasked with cutting down a colossal tree called the Gigas Cedar. They're swinging their ax when their friend Alice arrives with lunch. As they eat, the three friends decide to go to a fabled cave.

2.title: The Demon Tree
2.plot: Kirito wakes up to find himself inside a mysterious world evoking a fantasy game. His memory fuzzy, he tries to log out, but is unable to return to the real world. After wandering aimlessly, he finds himself underneath a colossal tree.

3.title: The End Mountains
3.plot: Kirito makes up his mind to journey to Centoria. Since he'll need Eugeo's help, he also decides to fell the Gigas Cedar. Meanwhile, Alice's little sister, Selka is worried about Eugeo, and opens up to Kirito about her concerns.

4.title: Departure
4.plot: Kirito and Eugeo realize Selka has taken off to the End Mountains alone, and decide to chase after her. As they enter the cave, they encounter goblins, presumably from the Dark Territory, and must engage in a battle.

5.title: Ocean Turtle
5.plot: In the real world, Kazuto Kirigaya lies unconscious. At Kikuoka's request, Kazuto is moved to a well-equipped hospital, but when Asuna and Suguha try to visit, they're turned away. Suspicious, Asuna and the others split up to find out more about Rath.

6.title: Project Alicization
6.plot: Asuna infiltrates Rath, the research lab in the Ocean Turtle, where she relentlessly grills Kikuoka about Kazuto's whereabouts. Kikuoka reveals that behind the development of the Soul Translator is a mind-blowing objective of epic scale.

7.title: Swordcraft Academy
7.plot: Two years have gone by since Kirito and Eugeo left Rulid Village. In the capital city, Centoria, both boys have attained their goal of being admitted to the North Centoria Imperial Swordcraft Academy.

8.title: Swordsman's Pride
8.plot: Kirito finds himself in a duel against the Elite Disciple Volo Levantein, using real swords. As the curious crowd looks on, Kirito is encouraged by Sortiliena, and the duel begins.

9.title: Nobleman's Responsibilities
9.plot: Now an Elite Disciple along with Kirito, Eugeo struggles with the question of what he should infuse in his sword so he can become stronger. When he's taunted by First-Seat Elite Disciple Raios and Second-Seat Humbert, Eugeo decides to accept Humbert's request for a duel.

10.title: Taboo Index
10.plot: Ronie and Tiese are late getting to the dorm. Kirito rushes out in search of them, but no sooner has he gone than Frenica appears. She tells Eugeo about how she's suffered at Humbert's hands, and that Tiese and Ronie went to confront him about it.

11.title: Central Cathedral
11.plot: Kirito and Eugeo are now considered criminals for having violated the Taboo Index and are thrown into the underground prison in the Central Cathedral. Meanwhile, on the Ocean Turtle in the real world, Asuna is watching over Kazuto as he's being treated.

12.title: The Sage of the Library
12.plot: Kirito and Eugeo escape from their cell, only to find their way blocked by Eldrie Synthesis Thirty-One, under orders from Alice to lie in wait for them. Kirito and Eugeo struggle against him until Eugeo realizes that he's seen Eldrie somewhere before.

13.title: Ruler and Mediator
13.plot: Cardinal finishes her explanation of the Administrators Origins and gives Kirito a word of warning. Then the three discuss plans to free Alice and save the world from the Administrators control. They're going to need some weapons.

14.title: The Crimson Knight
14.plot: After being entrusted with the fate of the world by Cardinal, Kirito and Eugeo head to the top floor of the Central Cathedral. They find their confiscated swords, only to be attacked by the bow-wielding Integrity Knight Deusolbert Synthesis Seven.

15.title: The Relentless Knight
15.plot: Kirito and Eugeo are on their way up the stairs of the Central Cathedral when they encounter two girls named Linel and Fizel. As they stand, wondering what two children are doing there, they let their guard down and.

16.title: The Osmanthus Knight
16.plot: Though riddled with wounds, Kirito manages to activate his Perfect Weapon Control art. Continuing on their way to the top floor of the Central Cathedral, Kirito and Eugeo find themselves standing before a strange-looking floating platform.

17.title: Truce
17.plot: When Kirito and Alice both unleash the Perfect Weapon Control art in the Cloudtop Garden, the impact rips a hole into the seemingly impregnable Central Cathedral wall, which sends them both flying outside.

18.title: The Legendary Hero
18.plot: Eugeo reaches the ninetieth floor of the Central Cathedral, which turns out to be a vast bathing area. The perplexed Eugeo encounters Bercouli Synthesis One soaking in the bath. Meanwhile, Kirito and Alice are still climbing the Central Cathedral wall.

19.title: Alicization 18.5: Recollection
19.plot: Recap of the first 18 episodes of Alicization.

1.title: The World of Swords
1.plot: In the near future, a virtual reality game called Sword Art Online has been released where players control their avatars with their bodies. One day players discover they cannot log out, as the game creator is holding them captive unless they defeat the final boss. However, if they die in the game, they die in real life. Their struggle for survival starts now.

2.title: Beater
2.plot: It's been one month since the players' entrapment in the game. Nearly 2000 people have died and the first floor hasn't been cleared yet.

3.title: The Red-Nosed Reindeer
3.plot: Kirito faces the consequences after witnessing the deaths of some of his friends in reality.

4.title: The Black Swordsman
4.plot: Dragon Tamer Silca leaves her group and pays the ultimate price. But before she is killed, Kirito offers her a choice that could have saved her life.

5.title: A Crime Within the Walls
5.plot: A player has been killed inside a safe zone and not by one of the known means. Asuna and Krito take it upon themselves to find out how and why this happened.

6.title: Illusionary Avenger
6.plot: After much investigating, Kirito figured out how players are dying in the safe zone and now he has to figure out why. Unfortunately danger is just around the corner.

7.title: The Warmth of the Heart
7.plot: Kirito seeks the help of Asuna's friend, Lisbeth, to craft a custom made sword.

8.title: Black and White Sword Dance
8.plot: Kirito begins a rivalry with Asuna's bodyguard, who is also a member of the Knights of the Blood Oath.

9.title: The Blue-Eyed Demon
9.plot: To save a group of players, including Asuna, from a boss character, Kirito is forced to play his trump card.

10.title: Seeing Red
10.plot: Kirito duels the leader of the Knights of the Blood Oath in exchange for Asuna's freedom.

11.title: The Morning Dew Girl
11.plot: A newly married couple is enjoying their time away from the frontlines. Unfortunately, a new guest will take them all the way back to the beginning.

12.title: Yui's Heart
12.plot: Yulier is second-in-command of the Liberation Army and has approached Kirito and Asuna for help. She needs to save her friend and her guild.

13.title: The Depths of Hell
13.plot: Kirito and Asuna's vacation is cut short when Heathcliff requests their return.

14.title: The End of the World
14.plot: It's game over. Kirito and Asuna spend their last moments together. Will they find one another again?

15.title: Return
15.plot: Kirigaya is adjusting to his life outside of the game, but he hasn't forgotten about Asuna. During a recent visit to the hospital he meets Sugou Nobuyuki.

16.title: The Land of Fairies
16.plot: A new MMO allows users to fly and encourages player killing. Kirito has joined this new game in search of Asuna and is pleasantly surprised with what he finds.

17.title: The Captive Queen
17.plot: As Kirito learns about the game and the hatred between the races from Leafa, Asuna learns the truth of her role from the Fairy King.

18.title: To the World Tree
18.plot: Leafa is making enemies when she leaves her area to team up with Kirito. On their way to neutral territory rules and areas are discussed.

19.title: The Lugru Corridor
19.plot: Leafa realizes something isn't right when recon sends an ominous message. What does it mean and will Leafa and Kirito have time to figure it out?

20.title: General of the Blazing Flames
20.plot: Kirito poses as an ambassador during a major meeting. If he can survive a fight against the Salamanders' General Eugene, his plan to prevent war might work.

21.title: The Truth About ALfheim
21.plot: While Asuna continues her attempt to escape, another woman in Kirito's life tries to make sense of her emotions.

22.title: Grand Quest
22.plot: Kirito's determination to save Asuna borders on sloppy and insane. His recklessness is stopped when Leafa suddenly logs out.

23.title: Bonds
23.plot: Even though a wall has been built between Kirito and Sugu he is determined to save Asuna. The next time he challenges the final dungeon he won't be alone.

24.title: Plated Hero
24.plot: Kirito, Asuna, and Yui are finally together again, but the locks placed on Asuna are unbreakable. Before they have a chance to come up with a plan, the Fairy King makes his grand entrance.

25.title: Sekai no Shushi
25.plot: Kazuto has beaten death twice, but there's one more thing he must do before he can see Asuna in the real world.

1.title: Gun World
1.plot: 2 years after the events of sword art online, Kirito is approached by a government agent with a new proposition after the apparent murder of pro players of the new main stream MMO Gun Gale Online.

2.title: Ice Sniper
2.plot: In a flashback, on September 14, 2025, Sinon, who had accidentally fallen down a trap chute while navigating a dungeon below SBC Gurokken in GGO, discovers a boss-class monster and decides to die while trying to defeat it. To her surprise, the position she chose for her attack was out of the monster's attack range, and thus, by conserving her ammo and accurately hitting the boss's weak spot, she is eventually able to defeat it and acquire a new sniper rifle, the PGM Ultima Ratio Hecate II. In the present day, during an ambush on an enemy squadron, Sinon attempts to ...

3.title: Memories of Blood
3.plot: In real life, Sinon is afraid of the sight of guns because of a robbery gone bad. Kirito tells Asuna he plans to log into Gun Gal Online.

4.title: GGO (Gun Gale Online)
4.plot: As some people are killed within the game Gun Gale Online, Kirito gets back in action, as the murderer may also be a survivor of Sword Art Online.....

5.title: Gun and Sword
5.plot: To bait out Death Gun, Kirito enters Bullet of Bullets, a tournament to decide the most powerful gunman in GGO.

6.title: Showdown in the Wilderness
6.plot: After witnessing Kirito's win in his first preliminary match, Death Gun asks Kirito if he is the real deal. Before he can answer Kirito notices his tattoo of Laughing Coffin and wonders if he's run into him before.

7.title: Crimson Memories
7.plot: Suguha confronts Kazuto about his activities in the online world as he grapples with having killed people in the Sword Art Online incident.

8.title: Bullet of Bullets
8.plot: Certain that Death Gun is competing in the BoB final, Kirito approaches Sinon beforehand about exchanging information, and begins to investigate the new players in the tournament.

9.title: Death Gun
9.plot: Kirito and Sinon hunt Death Gun through the Bullet of Bullets tournament. Asuna realizes the danger Kirito is in and sets out to find answers

10.title: Pursuer of Death
10.plot: Sinon is attacked from outta nowhere by Death Gun. Luckily Kirito manages to rescue her, but they are pursued by Death Gun.

11.title: The Meaning of Strength
11.plot: As Kirito and Sinon lay low in a desert cave, Kirito ponders on how Death Gun murdered the other players.

12.title: Bullet of a Phantom
12.plot: With the Bullet of Bullets tournament coming to a close, Kirito and Sinon set a trap for Death Gun, but another player might jeopardize it.

13.title: Phantom Bullet
13.plot: With Kirito is losing to Death Gun, Sinon looks for a way to save him.

14.title: A Small Step
14.plot: The Bullet of Bullets tournament comes to a close. Sinon confronts her inner demons.

15.title: The Queen of the Lake
15.plot: Kirito returns to ALO, bringing Asada with him, in order to obtain the sword, Excalibur.

16.title: King of the Giants
16.plot: At the entrance to Thrymheim, Yui explains that the quest they were given was created by the Cardinal System's Automatic Quest Generation Function and that if they did not succeed in their quest, a final war event, Ragnarok, would be triggered. Sometime later, at the end of the second floor of Thrymheimr, the group encounters two minotaurs, and they are forced to rely on Sword Skills that could deal elemental damage to them in addition to physical damage, but also leave the player rigid for a few seconds after the skill is used up. With Kirito revealing his new ...

17.title: Excalibur
17.plot: After clearing the first two stages the ice giant of the third stage proves more than the group can handle. Freyja tells Kirito the secret to defeating him.

18.title: The Forest House
18.plot: After hearing that a new update from New Year's Eve opens up floors 21-30 of new Aincrad, Kirito and the others race to reach floor 22 with the hope of once again purchasing the home he shared with Asuna and Yui.

19.title: Absolute Sword
19.plot: Asuna has a confrontation with her mother about her current schooling, and goes on to duel Zekken.

20.title: Sleeping Knights
20.plot: Zekken, leader of the Sleeping Knights guild wants to defeat a powerful floor boss. Needing a seventh Asuna agrees to join them.

21.title: Swordsman's Memorial
21.plot: Asuna and Sleeping Knights prepare to raid the 27th Floor Boss, but have to take out a rival guild blocking their way.

22.title: Journey's End
22.plot: After the Sleeping Knights guild disbands Asuna sets out to find Zekken (Yuuki), who reveals her tragic story.

23.title: Beginning of a Dream
23.plot: Yuuki lives out her dream. Asuna begins to repair her broken relationship with her mother.

24.title: Mother's Rosario
24.plot: In the season finale, Asuna, Yuuki as well as all of their friends continue to live happily in the world of Alfheim and New Aincrad. From duels and quests to taking bosses head on, the group is determined to make the most of their time together, by any means. However, when Asuna receives urgent news of Yuuki's condition, the line between her two worlds will become thinner than ever. And she will learn how the human spirit, as well as the love which sustains it, transcends all life.

imdb.plot outline: The year is 2022, and gamers have lined up on launch day for Sword Art Online, a hotly-anticipated MMORPG that lets players connect to an immersive virtual reality world with special helmets called Nerve Gear. Kirito is one such gamer who's eager to jump back into action, having spent a great deal of time as a beta tester, and quickly becomes friends with newbie warrior Klein. But soon, Sword Art Online's 10,000 players discover that not only are they unable to log out, the only way they can return to their physical bodies is by beating the 100-level tower's final boss - death in the game means death in the real world. Now, with no one else to turn to, Kirito and the other participants must survive the game as best they can.

The story takes place beginning in year 2022. A new game called _Sword Art Online_ (qv) (SAO for short), has come out on the NerveGear. A new technology that allows players to be inside the game. Beta tester and solo player Kirito re-enters SAO where he soon meets and befriends a newbie player. Then, the game's secrets spill from the shadows...

The story begins in year 2022, a new video game called _Sword Art Online_ (qv) (SAO for short) has just been released. The latest technology (the NerveGear) allows a player to be "literally in the game". Beta tester and solo player Kirito, re-enters this game. He then meets and befriends a newbie player named Klein. Soon, all the game's secrets spill from the shadows...

After SAO is finally over, everyone is finally able to relax and just enjoy playing their favorite games and MMORPGs. But out of nowhere, Kirito is asked to meet with a government agent who had previously investigated SAO. Kirito was then informed of a man seemingly killing players in the real world, by shooting them in a game. Then Kirito decides to investigate this. He enters the game Gun Gale Online (GGO for short), as usual, he befriends another player in GGO. Then secrets they're searching for fall right at their feet.
